The paper discusses a theoretical model connecting deep learning to finding the ground state of a Hamiltonian, which is a topic typically studied in the machine learning subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses regularization schemes and annealing schemes, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of topology trivialization is a technique that is often used in control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, and cs.IT, in that order.
